      "note": "abstract",
      "abstract": "SCS/SB 1249 - This act provides that the Director of the Department of Public Safety shall have cause to deny any application for a peace officer license or entrance into a basic training course when the applicant previously had a peace officer license or certification revoked or surrendered or when the applicant is not a citizen of the United States. \r\n\r\n\tThis act identical to HB 981 (2025), and to a provision contained in HS/HCS/HBs 3068 & 3049 (2026), and is similar to HB 981 (2025).\r\nTRISTAN BENSON, JR."
    }
  ],
  "other_titles": [
    {
      "note": "",
      "title": "Allows the Director of Public Safety to deny certain individuals a peace officer license or entry into basic training courses"
    }
  ],
